Description: Fragment of fattened handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora at neck join. Clay near fine mid red-brown. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Name Polykles. From same die as a piece from Kaunos, B.Schmaltz, Die Hellenistischen Amphorenstempel vom Kaunos (Asia Minor Studien 79) 52, KA 117. Trimmed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0547)
